            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">I really hate to sound like a whiner, but this patch kind of smells crappy to archer classes.<br>
<br>
Arrows sticking out of people and visible in the air?  errrr, ok, our stealth ability in RvR gets a nice little nerf again for that.  Will people start sprouting gouts of flame from their asses in the general direction a wizard throws a bolt spell at them now?  What is /face for again?  <br>
<br>
The bow shot getting interrupted after you've drawn is a total kick in the nuts to the solo archer player.  We will probably go from being able to score 3 or 4 hits on a mob with the bow, to 2 or 3.  Then have to melee it out.  I really feel sorry for the higher level archers that haven't spent any points in their melee skills.<br>
<br>
I'm really not trying to get pissed about this stuff, because it's still on test, but I'm pretty sure no one is going to protest against any type of archer class nerf, except archers.  And they are just viewed as a pack of whiners and d00ds.<br>
<br>
/sigh  <br>
<br>
I just want to play a guy with a bow.  When are they going to finish my class already?  I'm tired of adjusting.....</font></p>
             
