<hr></blockquote><br>
<br>
I think the class is Scout not Race Horse<br>
<br>
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1">quote:</font><hr><br>
I have NO safe fall ability to compensate for my knowledge of the terrain I am scouting. <br>
<hr></blockquote><br>
<br>
knowledge of terrain is something you can pick up in general, without having a skill to show it, but saying that I think a removal of the fist level of damage would be a good idea .. if, however, you fall 30ft then Scouts should take the same damage as everyone else.<br>
<br>
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1">quote:</font><hr><br>
How exactly am I supposed to scout anything? <br>
<hr></blockquote><br>
<br>
with stealth and group chat.<br>
<br>
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1">quote:</font><hr><br>
So, yeah, we've been reduced to assassins at range. Not our fault. Some of us REALLY want to be scouts.<br>
<hr></blockquote><br>
<br>
Scouts are not forced to be ranged assassins, its merely an option that some feel is not right.<br>
<br>
If you feel there is a problem with people complaining about assassin shots and you agree .. then why argue ?? .. instead .. try and get some things put into the class instead .. like small safe fall .. faster stealth movement for all classes with stealth (though I believe you get faster with more points).. basic tracking.<br>
<br>
<br>
just my 2cp worth</font></p>
             
